{
  "text": "Excision of localized primary melanomas provides a curative treatment for most patients; however, survival for patients with disseminated disease treated with systematic therapies remains poor. Clonal diversity has been associated with poor prognosis and treatment resistance in cancer [CITATION_1] , and we therefore examined genetic diversity in melanoma metastases.",
